examples.en: This crime was done deliberately.
They will deliberate the question.
My ex-wife deliberately sabotages my access to the children.
He deliberately tried to trip me.
All the files were deliberately destroyed.
Managers deliberately obscured the real situation from federal investigators.
I deliberately dropped into broad Yorkshire.
The votes were deliberately miscounted.
He was either normally stupid or being deliberately obtuse.
He deliberately rammed his car into mine.
Deliberately making people suffer is immoral.
The sentiment comes to be deliberately unrolled.
She spoke in a clear, deliberate manner.
'But why?' said Charles, being deliberately obtuse.
We believe that her comments were deliberately meant to mislead.
They deliberately slanted the story to make themselves look good.
They deliberately rammed my car from behind.
He advocates a slow and deliberate approach to the problem.
We believe that her comments were deliberately meant to mislead the public.
Some people say she deliberately tanked the match.
Evidence suggests that the private car was deliberately uncoupled.
The press had been deliberately excluded from the event.
For radio itself deliberately obsoletes today what it built yesterday.
The photograph of the two leaders shaking hands was deliberately staged.
His other arm lay across his chest, unnaturally, as if placed there deliberately, for a purpose.
